New York Times Best Selling Author

00:02:17.860 --> 00:02:29.640
of 21 novels, including Firefly
Lane, Home Front, Winter Garden,

00:02:29.640 --> 00:02:32.270
and the Nightingale,
her current book.

00:02:32.270 --> 00:02:36.240
And some of them have been
optioned already for movies.

00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:40.600
Kristin's books resonate with
readers across the country

00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:45.260
and the world because her
books have no borders.

00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:48.370
They are about ordinary
people who are thrust

00:02:48.370 --> 00:02:52.010
into extraordinary circumstances.

00:02:52.010 --> 00:02:59.610
In fact, I recently understand and
saw, some postings on the internet

00:02:59.610 --> 00:03:02.570 position:56%
by Reese Witherspoon, Brooke Shields

00:03:02.570 --> 00:03:05.720
and Elizabeth Banks,
among so many others.

00:03:05.720 --> 00:03:10.120
In the Nightingale, a story
about the Vianne and Isabelle,

00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:12.350
two sisters who lived in France

00:03:12.350 --> 00:03:16.150
under the German occupation
during World War II.

00:03:16.150 --> 00:03:22.580
She wrote, Kristin wrote, in love,
we find out who we want to be.

00:03:22.580 --> 00:03:25.830
In war, we find out who we are.

00:03:25.830 --> 00:03:32.670
It is impossible to express how
compelling I found Nightingale.

00:03:32.670 --> 00:03:38.220
In two consecutive week nights,
I was reading until 4 AM,

00:03:38.220 --> 00:03:42.790 position:56%
and then I was sorry I had finished.

